In diffrent IAM policy Condition play diifrent role:-

1. IAM policy:-
    Condition specify if the policy applicable or not
2. In trust policy:-
    Condition specify if the role can be assumed by the respective principle or not.

Condition in Trust policy:-
    In trust policy if principle is matched, the role is assumed, condition add one more level of filteration there.
    Ex:-
    > make sure that role is assumed by specific external party 
            {
              "Effect": "Allow",
              "Principal": { "AWS": "arn:aws:iam::<account_of_vendor>:role/VendorRole"},
              "Action": "sts:AssumeRole",
              "Condition": {"StringEquals": {"sts:ExternalId": "<unique id of vendor>"}}
            }
    > A user assume only if his MFA active
        "Principal": { "AWS": "arn:aws:iam::<any_third_party_account>:user/<user_of _third party>"},
        "Condition": {"Bool": {"aws:MultiFactorAuthPresent": "true"}}
    > if this role is assumed by any AWs service
        "Principal": {"Service": "lambda.amazonaws.com"},
        "Condition": {"ArnEquals": {"aws:SourceArn": "arn:aws:lambda:us-east-1:111122223333:function:my-function"}
                    "StringEquals": {"aws:SourceAccount": "111122223333"}}
    > Allow role to assumed by a specific lambda lies in another account 
              "Principal": {"AWS": "arn:aws:iam::<vendor_account>:role/<role_in _vendor_acc_of_lambda"},
              "Condition": {"StringEquals": {"sts:ExternalId": "your-unique-external-id"}}}
